The African Action Congress (AAC) has dispelled rumours making the rounds that the particulars of its presidential candidate, Comrade Omoyele Sowore have not been filled on the Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) portal. The AAC in a statement signed by its National Publicity Secretary, Comrade Femi Adeyeye, on Thursday described such news as fake and should be dispelled in its entirety. The party said that already, a total of 84 names of candidates, including Mr Omoyele Sowore and the vice presidential candidate, Mr Haruna Magashi, had been uploaded and approved on the INEC portal. It added: “INEC also pasted these names and particular in their offices nationwide. “Another batch of over 200 candidates are undergoing the approval process in the party and definitely would meet up with the timeline set by INEC on July 15, 2022. “Our party takes due diligence very seriously and Nigerians can be sure that the African Action Congress (AAC) won’t just upload and approve candidates like others; candidates who don’t have certificates, who lack character, competence and integrity. “We enjoin members of our great party, candidates and members of the public to disregard the rumour. “We expect that INEC will lead the public correctly on issues concerning the party and this particular issue, release a statement to put the body in correct light before Nigerians.”